<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<transcript>
  <text start="0.000" dur="3.500">Welcome back to Basics with Babish.</text>
  <text start="3.700" dur="4.100">Today we&#39;re making the perfect scrambled eggs.</text>
  <text start="8.200" dur="3.800">I&#39;m going to show you three different methods.</text>
  <text start="12.500" dur="4.200">First up is the <font color="#E5E5E5">French style</font>, low and slow.</text>
  <text start="17.100" dur="3.600">Crack your eggs into a cold non-stick pan.</text>
  <text start="21.000" dur="4.800">Add a generous knob of butter before applying any heat.</text>
  <text start="26.200" dur="5.000">Place over medium-low heat, stirring constantly
with a rubber spatula.</text>
  <text start="31.800" dur="4.300">Season with salt and pepper at the very end.</text>
  <text start="36.500" dur="3.900">The key is patience and constant movement.</text>
  <text start="40.800" dur="4.100">Remove from heat just before they look done.</text>
</transcript>
